.TH ZOPEN-INSTALL "1" "June 2026" "zopen tools 0.8.5" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
zopen-install \- manual page for zopen-install 0.8.5
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B zopen-install
[\fI\,OPION\/\fR] [\fI\,PACKAGE\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
zopen\-install is a utility to download/install a zopen community package.
.IP
[PACKAGE] is a package to install. Multiple packages can be specified.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-all\fR
download/install all zopen community packages.
.TP
\fB\-\-cache\-only\fR
do not install dependencies.
.TP
\fB\-\-download\-only\fR
download package to current directory.
.TP
\fB\-\-help\fR
print this help.
.TP
\fB\-\-install\-or\-upgrade\fR
installs the package if not installed,
or upgrades the package if installed.
.TP
\fB\-\-bypass\-prereq\-checks\fR
Ignores pre\-req checks
.TP
\fB\-\-local\-install\fR
download and unpackage to current directory.
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-deps\fR
do not install dependencies.
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-set\-active\fR
do not change the pinned version.
.TP
\fB\-\-nosymlink\fR
do not integrate into filesystem through
symlink redirection.
.TP
\fB\-r\fR, \fB\-\-reinstall\fR
reinstall already installed zopen community packages.
.HP
\fB\-\-release\-line\fR [stable, dev] the release line to build off of.
.TP
\fB\-\-select\fR
select a version to install.
.TP
\fB\-\-skip\-upgrade\fR
do not upgrade.
.TP
\fB\-\-force\fR
force install, bypassing locks.
.TP
\fB\-u\fR, \fB\-\-update\fR, \fB\-\-upgrade\fR
updates installed zopen community packages.
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
print verbose messages.
.TP
\fB\-\-version\fR
print version.
.TP
\fB\-y\fR, \fB\-\-yes\fR
automatically answer yes to prompts.
.PP
